class Solution {
    public int hammingDistance(int x, int y) {
        int xor = x ^ y;
        int count = 0;
        while (xor != 0) {
            count += xor & 1;
            xor >>>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log max(x, y))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses bitwise XOR to find different bits between x and y, then counts the number of 1s in the result using bitwise operations. It is efficient as it directly manipulates bits and has a constant space complexity.

